<div class="docs-getstarted-page">

  <h1 class="docs-getstarted-title">Getting Started</h1>
  <p class="docs-getstarted-desc">Add SoftUI to your project in seconds. No build tools required.</p>

  <!-- Install -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="install">
    <h2>Install</h2>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>npm install softui-css
# or
yarn add softui-css
# or
pnpm add softui-css
# or
bun add softui-css</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CDN -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="cdn">
    <h2>CDN</h2>
    <p>Drop these two lines into your <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> and you're ready to go:</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/softui-css/dist/softui.min.css"&gt;
&lt;script src="https://unpkg.com/softui-css/dist/softui.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- JavaScript -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="javascript">
    <h2>JavaScript</h2>
    <p>Most components are pure CSS. Some interactive components require <code>softui.js</code> — a lightweight, dependency-free script (~4KB min).</p>
    <p>Include it at the end of your <code>&lt;body&gt;</code>:</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>&lt;script src="https://unpkg.com/softui-css/dist/softui.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:14px;color:var(--sui-text-muted);">Components that need JS: Accordion, Calendar, Carousel, Chart, Collapsible, Color Picker, Combobox, Command, Context Menu, Data Table, Dock, Drag &amp; Drop, Dropdown, File Upload, Input OTP, Menubar, Modal, Popover, Rating, Resizable, Sheet, Sidebar, Slider, Swap, Tabs, Toggle Group, and form enhancements (Password Toggle, Number Input, Tags Input).</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Frameworks -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="frameworks">
    <h2>Using with Frameworks</h2>
    <p>SoftUI is plain CSS — it works with any framework. Just import the styles and use the classes.</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>/* React — import in your entry file (App.jsx or index.jsx) */
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.css';
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.js';

function App() {
  return (
    &lt;button className="sui-btn sui-btn-primary"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;
  );
}


/* Vue — import in main.js */
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.css';
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.js';

&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;button class="sui-btn sui-btn-primary"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/template&gt;


/* Svelte — import in +layout.svelte or app.html */
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.css';
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.js';

&lt;button class="sui-btn sui-btn-primary"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;


/* Astro — import in your layout */
---
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.css';
---
&lt;script src="/node_modules/softui-css/dist/softui.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;


/* Next.js — import in _app.js or layout.tsx */
import 'softui-css/dist/softui.min.css';
/* Add softui.min.js via Script component or next/script */</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:14px;color:var(--sui-text-muted);">Tip: For JS-dependent components (modals, dropdowns, etc.), make sure <code>softui.js</code> loads after the DOM is ready. In React/Vue/Svelte, the import handles this automatically.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Start -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="quickstart">
    <h2>Quick Start</h2>
    <p>Here's a minimal HTML page with a neumorphic button and card:</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
  &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;
  &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/softui-css/dist/softui.min.css"&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body class="sui-d-flex sui-justify-center sui-align-center sui-min-vh-100"&gt;

  &lt;div class="sui-card sui-raised sui-p-5 sui-text-center"&gt;
    &lt;h3&gt;Hello SoftUI&lt;/h3&gt;
    &lt;p class="sui-text-muted sui-mt-2 sui-mb-3"&gt;
      A neumorphic card with a soft raised shadow.
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;button class="sui-btn sui-btn-primary"&gt;Get Started&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;script src="https://unpkg.com/softui-css/dist/softui.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Dark Mode -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="darkmode">
    <h2>Dark Mode</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-theme="dark"</code> to your <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> element. Every component adapts automatically.</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>&lt;html data-theme="dark"&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:16px;">To prevent a flash of light mode when the page loads, add this blocking script in your <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> before any stylesheets:</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;style&gt;body{opacity:0}&lt;/style&gt;
  &lt;script&gt;
    var t = localStorage.getItem('sui-theme');
    if (t === 'dark' || (!t && matchMedia('(prefers-color-scheme:dark)').matches))
      document.documentElement.setAttribute('data-theme', 'dark');
  &lt;/script&gt;
  &lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="softui.min.css"&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:12px;font-size:14px;color:var(--sui-text-muted);">The inline <code>opacity:0</code> hides the page until SoftUI's CSS loads (which sets <code>opacity:1</code>), eliminating any flash. The script reads the saved theme preference before the first paint.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Customization -->
  <section class="docs-getstarted-section" id="customize">
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>SoftUI is built on CSS custom properties. Override them anywhere to match your brand:</p>
    <div class="docs-getstarted-code">
<pre><code>:root {
  --sui-primary: #7C5CFC;
  --sui-radius: 12px;
  --sui-shadow-raised: 6px 6px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.15),
                       -6px -6px 12px rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
}</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:12px;">See the <a href="/theming/" style="color:var(--sui-primary);font-weight:600;">Theming Guide</a> for the full list of variables — colors, shadows, radius, fonts, transitions, and dark mode.</p>
  </section>

